The paper deals with cryptographic techniques for ensuring privacy in polls, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficiency and practicality of the proposed techniques, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of quantum cryptography in the proposed solutions could also place the paper under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB).
